<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Resa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello.<P>Had a couple questions if you can help me with wis to mana ratio.<P>What is the formula of wis to mana before AND after 200 wis.<P>-Resa</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shohanna Curesurtales</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/misc/manacalc/manacalc_wis.asp" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.castersrealm.com/misc/manacalc/manacalc_wis.asp</A> <BR>go to mana calculator.<BR>   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>sho<P>[This message has been edited by Shohanna Curesurtales (edited 06-05-2001).]<p>[This message has been edited by Shohanna Curesurtales (edited 06-05-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Resa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"Please note this calculator is only accurate to a maximum of 200 wisdom."<P>Theres a formula too... Im trying to remember... GRRRR<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wyndal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I asked this same question on the druid board a couple of days ago and this was the reply:<P>"to calculate mana based upon wisdom do the following<P>((wis*lvl)/5)+2*lvl plus any mana pt due to items = total mana pool.<P>thus for a 30 lvl player with a wis of 150 you would have<P>(30*150)/5+2*30= 960<P>or lvl/5*150+2*lvl = mana <P>if you look at it this way then you can see how many mana pts you have per lvl change."<P>Hope this is what you're looking for )<P>Wyndal<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks Wyn. I knew about the (level*wis)/5 part but not the rest. Now my calculations match with castersrealm.<P>But they left off a part.<P>IF your total wisdom is more than 200 then you must do the following...<P>Take your wisdom and subtract 200. Now, use 200 as your wisdom for calculations as normal but when you add in +mana items you also need to add in the value you obtained by subtracting 200.<P>I have 211 wis, 210 in +mana and am level 57 so here's how it goes.<P>Step 1.<P>If(wis > 200)<BR>211 - 200 = 11<P>Else do nothing<P>Step 2<P>If(wis > 200) wis = 200<P>(200*57)/5+2*30 + 210 + 11 = 2615 mana<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=58690" TARGET=_blank>Check my math</A><P>For you <BR>(30*150)/5+2*30 +0 mana +0 extra wis= 960<P>Each point of wis beyond 200 is +1 mana. That is the soft cap.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">((wis/5)+2)*lvl<P>works also, if that's easier to remember.<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
